thread.title: Iowa, New Hampshire Voters Hold Dim View of Clinton, Poll Finds
thread.title_full: Iowa, New Hampshire Voters Hold Dim View of Clinton, Poll Finds - WSJ

author: Rebecca Ballhaus
title: Iowa, New Hampshire Voters Hold Dim View of Clinton, Poll Finds
text:
Voters in two presidential swing states, Iowa and New Hampshire, hold a strongly negative view of Hillary Clinton and choose several potential Republican opponents over her in test match-ups.
New Wall Street Journal/NBC News/Marist polls of the two states found that Bernie Sanders is viewed more positively by registered voters than is Mrs. Clinton and draws stronger support as a general election candidate against several potential...
